7. Multi-Venue & Hedge-Mode Trading Infrastructure

Why It Matters

Coinbase only allows one net position per asset.
Binance, OKX, and MEXC allow hedge mode (long and short at once).
This enables ELBOT to scalp both directions or hedge spot holdings.

Supported Exchanges

Exchange	Hedge Mode	Type	Notes
Binance Futures	✅	Futures	Ideal for long/short hedging
MEXC Futures	✅	Futures	Hedge + minimal KYC
OKX Futures	✅	Futures	Institutional-grade
Kraken Futures	⚠️ Partial	Futures	Regulated option
Coinbase	❌	Spot	Long-term asset holding

Dual Context Design

{
  "spot": {"BTCUSDT": {"side": "LONG", "amount": 0.5}},
  "futures": {
    "BTCUSDT_LONG": {"amount": 1.0},
    "BTCUSDT_SHORT": {"amount": 1.0}
  }
}

Hedge Manager Example

class HedgeManager:
    def evaluate_hedge(self, spot_position, futures_signal):
        if spot_position['side'] == "LONG" and futures_signal['bias'] == "SHORT":
            execute_futures_short(symbol="BTCUSDT", size=spot_position['amount'])


